From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mykola Lysenko <mykolal@meta.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 11:30:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] selftests/bpf: keep test_progs running without verification key

test_progs registers the test verification certificate in the session
keyring during process startup. If the running kernel cannot instantiate
that asymmetric key, even metadata-only commands such as --list and
--count abort before non-signature tests can be selected or run.

Keep the harness usable by warning and continuing. Signature-dependent
tests can still report their own failures or skips, but unrelated tests
are no longer blocked by a global startup dependency.

Signed-off-by: Mykola Lysenko <mykolal@meta.com>
---
 tools/testing/selftests/bpf/test_progs.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/test_progs.c b/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/test_progs.c
index 7ba82974ee78..730f4c3be77a 100644
--- a/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/test_progs.c
+++ b/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/test_progs.c
@@ -2039,7 +2039,9 @@ int main(int argc, char **argv)
 	err = register_session_key((const char *)test_progs_verification_cert,
 				   test_progs_verification_cert_len);
 	if (err < 0)
-		return err;
+		fprintf(stderr,
+			"WARNING! Failed to register test_progs verification key: %s. Signature-dependent tests may fail.\n",
+			strerror(errno));
 
 	traffic_monitor_set_print(traffic_monitor_print_fn);
 
-- 
2.53.0
